            <h4>What is the current population of Weston?</h4>
            <p>
                Based on the latest 2022 data from the US census, the
                current population of Weston is 3,890.  Weston, West Virginia is the 5,507th largest city in the US.
            </p>

            

            

            <h4>What was the peak population of Weston?</h4>
            <p>
                
                    The peak population of Weston was in
                    1990, when its population was
                    5,175.
                    
                        In 1990, Weston was the
                        3,975th largest city in the US; now
                        its fallen to the 5,507th largest city in
                        the US.
                    
                    Weston is currently
                        <span style="color: red;">
                            24.8%
                            smaller
                        </span>
                        than it was in 1990.
                    </p>
                
            </p>
            
                
                    <h4>How quickly is Weston shrinking?</h4>
                
                <p>
                    
                        Weston has shrunk
                        9.3% 
                        since the year 2000.
                    


                    
                        Weston, West Virginia's growth is below average.
                        78% of similarly sized
                        cities are growing faster since 2000.
                    
                </p>
            

            

            

            

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
